  "body": "I talked to christian and gavin yesterday and they both agree that we should have a method which can estimate the gas usage of a transaction, without sending and using up the gas.\n\nThis method is now described in the specs: https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/JSON-RPC#eth_estimategas\n\nI already started a branch, but with my limited understanding of the EVM its very hard to get the gas used out of it: https://github.com/frozeman/go-ethereum/tree/estimateGas\n\nI basically create the method `eth_estimateGas`:\n\n``` js\ncase \"eth_estimateGas\":\n        args := new(CallArgs)\n        if err := json.Unmarshal(req.Params, &args); err != nil {\n            return err\n        }\n\n        // this need to return the gas used instead of bytes\n        v, err := api.xethAtStateNum(-1).Call(args.From, args.To, args.Value.String(), args.Gas.String(), args.GasPrice.String(), args.Data)\n        if err != nil {\n            return err\n        }\n\n                // this also needs to be changed, depending on the return value\n        if v == \"0x0\" {\n            *reply = nil\n        } else {\n            *reply = newHexNum(big.NewInt(v).Bytes())\n        }\n```\n\nI could trace the EVM down to https://github.com/frozeman/go-ethereum/blob/estimateGas/core/execution.go#L45\n\nBut i have no idea how to return the used gas instead of the VM output. @obscuren could you give me a hint?\n",
